Your timing is terrible.

00:43.910 --> 00:45.509
I was just about
to sit down for dinner.

00:45.511 --> 00:47.978
Without me?
Wow, I'm offended.

00:47.980 --> 00:49.980
What'd you cook?

00:49.982 --> 00:52.750
What makes you think I didn't
just microwave a pizza?

00:52.752 --> 00:54.952
Hmm, not your style.

00:54.954 --> 00:56.053
What'd you cook?

00:56.055 --> 00:59.790
Oh, nothing crazy,
just a little, uh...

00:59.792 --> 01:01.392
chicken cordon bleu.

01:01.394 --> 01:03.093
Mmm, sounds good.

01:03.095 --> 01:04.762
What kind of cheese
did you use?

01:04.763 --> 01:08.065
Cheese? Uh--

01:10.168 --> 01:12.736
Uh, you know,
just, uh classic

01:12.738 --> 01:14.505
<i>cordon bleu cheese.</i>

01:15.841 --> 01:18.042
Gruyère, yeah.

01:18.044 --> 01:21.111
Oh, you'll have
to save me a piece.

01:21.113 --> 01:23.380
Sure will,
but I know you didn't...

01:23.382 --> 01:25.716
call me to talk about food,
so what's up?

01:25.718 --> 01:28.252
<i>No, I didn't call</i>
<i>to talk about the food.</i>

01:28.254 --> 01:31.589
I called to talk about us.

01:31.591 --> 01:34.425
Is that so?

01:34.427 --> 01:38.596
♪ You left my heart out ♪

01:38.598 --> 01:44.168
♪ When the rest of me is down ♪

01:44.170 --> 01:47.938
♪ You, you enchanted me... ♪

01:47.940 --> 01:50.040
All I said was
you have a nice ass.

01:50.042 --> 01:53.160
Well, that is both flattering
and objectifying.

01:53.162 --> 01:54.995
<i>I didn't mean</i>
<i>to objectify you.</i>

01:54.997 --> 01:56.197
Forgive me.

01:56.199 --> 01:59.233
<i>I must say, you do have</i>
<i>very kissable lips.</i>

01:59.235 --> 02:02.903
So, what you just turn into
a player after midnight,

02:02.905 --> 02:04.471
<i>like a macking werewolf?</i>

02:04.473 --> 02:06.106
Yeah, it's character flaw.

02:06.108 --> 02:09.342
♪ Now I know what I have found ♪

02:11.346 --> 02:12.780
How do you even know
what my lips look like.

02:12.782 --> 02:14.148
You haven't seen me
in over two weeks.

02:14.150 --> 02:15.216
<i>I have a DVR.</i>

02:15.218 --> 02:16.884
I'm watching one of your
old show right now.

02:16.886 --> 02:18.652
Which show?

02:18.654 --> 02:21.722
The one about
fraternity hazing.

02:21.724 --> 02:24.191
<i>Ah, I remember that,</i>
<i>I looked good that day.</i>

02:24.193 --> 02:26.260
You look good every day.

02:26.262 --> 02:28.896
<i>So inquiring minds</i>
<i>wanna know.</i>

02:28.898 --> 02:30.531
Are you barren or not?

02:34.669 --> 02:35.736
<i>Too far?</i>

02:35.738 --> 02:39.006
Too personal, too soon.

02:39.008 --> 02:41.108
<i>Well, obviously,</i>
<i>I follow you.</i>

02:41.110 --> 02:42.743
I watch all your shows.

02:42.745 --> 02:45.579
<i>And I have to honestly say,</i>
<i>I think you're very brave</i>

02:45.581 --> 02:47.615
for putting everything
out there like that.

02:47.617 --> 02:51.151
You say brave, but right now,
it just seems stupid.

02:51.153 --> 02:54.488
Stupid is the last word

02:54.490 --> 02:57.491
anyone would associate
with Mary Jane Paul.

03:01.162 --> 03:05.266
♪ If there are boundaries,
I will try... ♪

03:05.268 --> 03:08.702
Oh, come on, Eddie Murphy
is a comedic genius.

03:08.704 --> 03:10.371
Jerry Lewis-like in his nuance.

03:10.373 --> 03:13.274
<i>Honey, the Parisians</i>
<i>are not stupid.</i>

03:13.276 --> 03:15.542
They love Lewis
and they love Murphy.

03:15.544 --> 03:17.745
Oh, come on, not "48 Hours?"

03:17.747 --> 03:20.347
<i>Not "Trading Places?"</i>

03:20.349 --> 03:21.949
Not even "Dreamgirls?"

03:21.951 --> 03:24.551
But "Norbit",
that's your favorite film.

03:24.553 --> 03:25.786
What are you
even talking about?

03:25.788 --> 03:27.955
You just went on
a 20-minute rant

03:27.957 --> 03:30.190
<i>about the sub-text</i>
<i>of the "Wizard of Oz."</i>

03:30.192 --> 03:32.326
You know, I think
I'm starting to figure you out.

03:32.328 --> 03:34.795
Mister No Interview, yeah.

03:34.797 --> 03:37.064
I know who you are, uh-huh.

03:37.066 --> 03:40.067
<i>You're the man that loves</i>
<i>to be behind the curtain.</i>

03:40.069 --> 03:42.403
<i>But really, you're just</i>
<i>the Cowardly Lion.</i>

03:42.405 --> 03:45.072
You're afraid you'll
have nothing to say.

03:48.043 --> 03:52.846
You know, no one's ever had
the balls to say that to me.

03:52.848 --> 03:54.214
<i>And trust me,</i>

03:54.216 --> 03:56.216
I'm never at a loss
for something to say.

03:56.218 --> 03:57.351
Clearly.

03:57.353 --> 03:59.787
<i>Uh, look,</i>
<i>it's almost 1:00 a.m.</i>

03:59.789 --> 04:04.591
and us working folks need
to get up in the morning.

04:04.593 --> 04:07.528
<i>Okay, good night.</i>

04:07.530 --> 04:08.864
Good night.

04:11.566 --> 04:14.101
<i>So hang up then.</i>

04:14.103 --> 04:16.570
Give me a chance.

04:16.572 --> 04:19.473
♪ Feel so enamored ♪

04:19.475 --> 04:22.176
♪ Hold me tight
within your clutch ♪

04:22.178 --> 04:23.410
<i>Paper or plastic?</i>

04:23.412 --> 04:25.913
Uh, I don't know,
it's tough.

04:25.915 --> 04:27.748
<i>Paper kills trees</i>

04:27.750 --> 04:30.217
but plastic is
non-biodegradable.

04:30.219 --> 04:31.352
Choose.

04:31.354 --> 04:33.404
Plastic.

04:33.406 --> 04:35.873
I hate myself.

04:35.875 --> 04:37.007
Malcolm or Martin?

04:37.009 --> 04:41.345
Uh, Martin when I was a kid

04:41.347 --> 04:42.579
and Malcolm now.

04:42.581 --> 04:45.949
<i>Marvin Gaye or John Lennon?</i>

04:45.951 --> 04:47.851
Lennon,
take away my black card.

04:49.171 --> 04:50.337
Uh, film or digital?

04:50.339 --> 04:51.372
Film.

04:51.374 --> 04:53.707
<i>Day and night,</i>
<i>digital has no soul.</i>

04:53.709 --> 04:55.342
Lunch or dinner?

04:55.344 --> 04:56.543
Dinner. <i>Great.</i>

04:56.545 --> 04:58.579
I'll pick you up
tomorrow around 7:00.

04:58.581 --> 05:00.814
Oh, come on now,
does that move really work?

05:00.816 --> 05:03.517
I don't know, you tell me,
are we having dinner?

05:03.519 --> 05:04.785
<i>We should, you owe me.</i>

05:04.787 --> 05:05.919
For what?

05:05.921 --> 05:07.454
<i>I thought you</i>
<i>gave me that intel</i>

05:07.456 --> 05:08.989
on Brian Ellis because
you wanted to help someone,

05:08.991 --> 05:10.557
mainly yourself.

05:10.559 --> 05:14.194
♪ Now I've got you
in my space ♪

05:14.196 --> 05:16.230
Hello, are you still there?

05:16.232 --> 05:17.865
<i>I'm still here.</i>

05:17.867 --> 05:21.301
Just taking a pause trying
to figure out what I'm doing.

05:21.303 --> 05:24.838
I thought you were
asking me out to dinner.

05:24.840 --> 05:27.741
Ah, as a lawyer,

05:27.743 --> 05:29.176
we're trained not
to ask a question

05:29.178 --> 05:31.645
that we don't already
know the answer to.

05:31.647 --> 05:34.982
♪ Now I've got you in space ♪

05:34.984 --> 05:37.184
I may have
just exposed myself.

05:39.120 --> 05:40.788
I would love to.

05:40.790 --> 05:42.124
Girl's gotta eat, right?

05:45.527 --> 05:47.628
I'll call you tomorrow
with the details.

05:47.630 --> 05:50.631
Okay.

05:50.633 --> 05:53.500
Oh, it's so late.

05:53.502 --> 05:55.068
I'm gonna regret this
in a few hours.

05:55.070 --> 05:56.804
No, you're not.

05:56.806 --> 05:58.305
<i>You're gonna have</i>
<i>a big smile on your face</i>

05:58.307 --> 06:00.140
<i>about this in a few hours.</i>

06:00.142 --> 06:02.109
Good night.

06:02.111 --> 06:03.177
Good night.

06:03.179 --> 06:08.415
♪ I'm latching on to you ♪
♪

06:17.826 --> 06:19.960
<i>Revealed that</i>
<i>the off-purchase revenue</i>

06:19.962 --> 06:23.046
<i>from a diamond mining company</i>
<i>operating in Bahrin area</i>

06:23.048 --> 06:25.549
<i>have funded a new set</i>
<i>of security forces</i>

06:25.551 --> 06:28.051
<i>loyal to the ruling party.</i>

06:39.364 --> 06:41.265
Hey. Hey.

06:41.267 --> 06:42.399
Are you okay?

06:42.401 --> 06:44.234
No, I'm fine.

06:45.370 --> 06:46.704
Can I come in?

06:48.373 --> 06:50.574
Come on.

06:58.283 --> 07:00.083
Okay, you wanna tell me
what's going on

07:00.085 --> 07:01.218
or are you gonna
make me guess?

07:01.220 --> 07:02.386
He's gone.

07:02.388 --> 07:05.055
Who?

07:05.057 --> 07:07.024
Eric.

07:07.026 --> 07:08.392
Oh, when you said,
"He's gone,"

07:08.394 --> 07:09.927
I thought maybe your dad died.

07:09.929 --> 07:12.496
I knew it was something 'cause
you didn't take the trash out.

07:12.498 --> 07:15.732
Well, Mary Jane,
in the back of my mind,

07:15.734 --> 07:21.705
I-- I harbored the hope that
we'd work things out, you know?

07:21.707 --> 07:24.675
I thought he left because

07:24.677 --> 07:27.644
he needed a break from me,
a vacation and--

07:27.646 --> 07:29.680
Oh, let him go play.

07:29.682 --> 07:32.482
In three months or so,
we'd work things out.

07:34.019 --> 07:37.120
Right, listen to this.

07:37.122 --> 07:39.289
<i>Hi, Mark, it's Eric.</i>

07:39.291 --> 07:42.826
<i>Look, Atlanta's a small town</i>
<i>and we know the same people.</i>

07:42.828 --> 07:45.395
<i>And I don't want you hearing</i>
<i>this from someone else.</i>

07:45.397 --> 07:46.530
<i>But I met someone,</i>

07:46.532 --> 07:49.600
<i>and I'm moving</i>
<i>to London next week.</i>

07:49.602 --> 07:50.667
<i>I'm happy.</i>

07:53.038 --> 07:55.305
<i>I'll be there</i>
<i>in a moment, please.</i>

07:55.307 --> 07:59.610
<i>Sorry, he, uh--</i>
<i>We have a kid.</i>

07:59.612 --> 08:02.312
<i>So now you know.</i>

08:02.314 --> 08:04.748
<i>Take care, Mark.</i>

08:04.750 --> 08:07.751
<i>Let's, uh--</i> Mary Jane.

08:07.753 --> 08:13.290
<i>I hope you-- Well, bye.</i>

08:13.292 --> 08:15.659
Look, that is some B.S.,
all right?

08:15.661 --> 08:17.427
He's just trying to hurt you,
it's probably not even true.

08:17.429 --> 08:18.795
But it hurts.

08:18.797 --> 08:20.898
I know, it hurts, okay?

08:20.900 --> 08:22.766
Trust me, I know, all right?

08:22.768 --> 08:25.936
But, it--
You have to get to work.

08:25.938 --> 08:28.939
<i>We</i> have to get to work,
all right?

08:28.941 --> 08:31.909
Was he seeing that
Richard guy the whole time?

08:31.911 --> 08:33.510
I mean, was--

08:33.511 --> 08:36.980
This Richard guy with the baby
there the whole time?

08:36.982 --> 08:38.582
No, you don't know that.

08:38.583 --> 08:40.951
It might've been some
kind of whirlwind romance.

08:40.953 --> 08:42.119
What are you telling me?

08:42.121 --> 08:43.854
That a month
after he dumps me,

08:43.856 --> 08:45.856
he meets somebody he wants
to leave the country for?

08:45.858 --> 08:47.557
So what does that
make me, Mary Jane?

08:47.559 --> 08:48.893
The makeup bang,

08:48.894 --> 08:51.061
the pre-game show,
the sugar daddy?

08:51.063 --> 08:52.496
I don't think
Eric cheated on you.

08:52.498 --> 08:54.414
Mary Jane, are you
freaking listening?!

08:54.416 --> 08:55.782
He has a kid!

08:55.784 --> 08:57.284
Bring it down,

08:57.286 --> 09:01.521
I'm right here, okay?

09:03.891 --> 09:05.525
And look.

09:09.330 --> 09:11.698
This is every gift
he ever gave me.

09:11.700 --> 09:13.834
Every gift
he ever gave me, Mary Jane.

09:13.836 --> 09:14.836
Okay, okay, okay.

09:14.837 --> 09:18.538
Everything.
Okay, baby, baby.

09:18.540 --> 09:20.540
Ohh.

09:20.542 --> 09:22.943
We have to go, okay?

09:22.945 --> 09:25.379
We have to go, all right?

09:25.381 --> 09:26.546
Mary Jane.

09:26.548 --> 09:28.682
We gotta go.

09:30.019 --> 09:32.519
Okay? Okay.

09:32.521 --> 09:34.054
Okay.

09:43.131 --> 09:44.465
Who is it?

09:44.466 --> 09:47.367
Deja, baby, it's me.

09:55.376 --> 09:56.476
Hi, Daddy.

09:56.478 --> 09:58.912
Hey, good morning to you.

09:58.914 --> 10:02.783
Where's, uh--
Where's your mom?

10:02.785 --> 10:04.017
She went out.

10:04.019 --> 10:05.852
Really? Yeah.

10:05.854 --> 10:07.721
When? Hmm.

10:13.094 --> 10:14.294
Oh.

10:16.397 --> 10:17.664
She probably
went out real quick

10:17.666 --> 10:19.700
'cause she knew I was
coming early today.

10:19.702 --> 10:22.903
Yeah. Hmm.

10:22.905 --> 10:23.970
Proud of you for getting
yourself ready.

10:23.972 --> 10:25.238
Thanks.

10:25.240 --> 10:27.532
Go on and finish your cereal
so I can get you to school.

10:38.654 --> 10:39.686
Hello?

10:39.688 --> 10:41.755
Hey.

10:41.757 --> 10:43.023
I need your Triple-A number.

10:43.025 --> 10:45.058
<i>Why, what's going on?</i>

10:45.060 --> 10:46.760
<i>Jeez, what happened</i>
<i>to your car now?</i>

10:46.762 --> 10:48.628
I'm pissed,
I'm over here at Tracy's.

10:48.630 --> 10:49.630
I knock on the door

10:49.631 --> 10:50.731
to find Deja all by herself.

10:50.733 --> 10:52.232
<i>She been by herself</i>
<i>all night.</i>

10:52.234 --> 10:53.233
I don't have a clue
where Tracy is.

10:53.235 --> 10:54.601
My God, is Deja okay?

10:54.603 --> 10:56.136
Looks to be,

10:56.138 --> 10:57.537
a little disheveled is all.

10:57.539 --> 10:59.506
And I wanna get her to school
so she can have a normal day,

10:59.508 --> 11:00.508
but my car won't start.

11:00.509 --> 11:01.508
So if I could please
use your card,

11:01.510 --> 11:02.509
I'd greatly appreciate it.

11:02.511 --> 11:03.677
Yeah, I will
text you the number.

11:03.679 --> 11:05.245
Have you made contact with
Tracy's parents?

11:05.247 --> 11:07.013
No, they haven't
heard anything.

11:07.015 --> 11:08.248
You don't think--

11:08.250 --> 11:09.649
What else is there to think?

11:09.651 --> 11:11.084
Oh, God.

11:11.086 --> 11:13.086
You got the number
of that P.I.

11:13.088 --> 11:14.121
you used to
find me a while back.

11:14.123 --> 11:15.222
<i>Yeah, Patrick,</i>

11:15.224 --> 11:16.923
he's expensive
and those costs add up.

11:16.925 --> 11:18.259
<i>So I don't think</i>
<i>that's for you.</i>

11:18.260 --> 11:20.327
Yeah, text me
his number anyway.

11:20.329 --> 11:22.095
Yeah, sure, no problem.

11:22.097 --> 11:24.097
I don't know, Letta.

11:24.099 --> 11:26.800
What if she been in an accident
or she was assaulted.

11:26.802 --> 11:29.469
Maybe-- Yeah, maybe, maybe.

11:29.471 --> 11:32.172
This is not what
I needed today.

11:32.174 --> 11:33.840
Poor Deja.

11:33.842 --> 11:35.075
Yeah.

11:35.077 --> 11:36.510
<i>Good luck, Patrick.</i>

11:36.512 --> 11:38.044
Well, thanks, uh.

11:38.046 --> 11:39.679
If I hear anything,
I'll let you know, okay?

11:39.681 --> 11:41.114
<i>All right, bye.</i>

11:45.319 --> 11:46.787
Miss Keller's gonna be mad.

11:46.789 --> 11:48.822
Oh, she'll understand,
everybody's late sometimes.

11:48.824 --> 11:50.524
Now I'll pick you up
at 3:00, okay?

11:50.526 --> 11:51.558
You promise?

11:51.560 --> 11:54.227
Of course, I promise.

11:54.229 --> 11:55.629
What about the bake sale?

11:55.631 --> 11:57.063
What bake sale?

11:57.065 --> 11:58.698
Mommy gives me money
to buy cupcakes

11:58.700 --> 11:59.800
in the bake sale on Monday.

11:59.802 --> 12:00.802
How much?

12:00.803 --> 12:02.068
$3.00.

12:05.641 --> 12:07.073
Oh...

12:08.543 --> 12:10.811
One, two.

12:12.647 --> 12:13.914
Thanks, Dad.

12:13.916 --> 12:16.750
All right, see you, darling.

12:25.026 --> 12:27.527
The president is schedule to
give a major speech tomorrow

12:27.529 --> 12:30.230
at the National Defense
University in Washington.

12:30.232 --> 12:33.767
The main topic, our country's
use or as some would charge

12:33.769 --> 12:36.336
our misuse
of unmanned aerial vehicles,

12:36.338 --> 12:37.637
<i>the drone program.</i>

12:37.639 --> 12:39.706
<i>Perhaps no other aspect</i>
<i>of modern warfare</i>

12:39.708 --> 12:42.108
<i>has been more controversial.</i>

12:42.110 --> 12:43.343
I'll be right back.

12:43.345 --> 12:46.830
<i>How no country at war</i>
<i>in human history</i>

12:46.832 --> 12:49.032
<i>has been more attentive</i>
<i>to preventing...</i>

12:49.034 --> 12:52.636
Excuse me, I am working
60 plus hours a week

12:52.638 --> 12:54.971
to make sure the boys
have everything they need.

12:54.973 --> 12:56.006
What more do you want from me?

12:56.008 --> 12:57.407
<i>More money.</i>

12:57.409 --> 12:59.910
I have full custody
of them now, Kara.

12:59.912 --> 13:01.244
It isn't about spite,
it's mathematics.

13:01.246 --> 13:02.646
<i>Wait a minute.</i>

13:02.648 --> 13:04.481
One minute you're complaining
that I'm working too much

13:04.483 --> 13:06.883
and now you're telling me that
I-- That you need more money?

13:06.885 --> 13:08.518
<i>Which one is it, John?</i>

13:08.520 --> 13:09.819
It's both, obviously.

13:09.821 --> 13:12.622
And however you wanna solve
this puzzle is not my problem.

13:12.624 --> 13:14.324
The problem is
tuition went up 12%,

13:14.326 --> 13:16.393
and I don't have it.
<i>Oh, well, you know what?</i>

13:16.395 --> 13:18.895
Maybe it's time to get
to know the real world.

13:18.897 --> 13:20.564
<i>Maybe they need to go</i>
<i>to public school.</i>

13:20.566 --> 13:22.532
No, not in Atlanta. Why?

13:22.534 --> 13:24.167
<i>Public school was</i>
<i>just fine for us,</i>

13:24.169 --> 13:25.569
and it'll be
just fine for them.

13:25.571 --> 13:27.337
Oh, yeah, 'cause that--
that makes good sense, Kara.

13:27.339 --> 13:29.472
