26:32.357 --> 26:34.290
the Piñero with
Benjamin Bratt in it.

26:34.292 --> 26:38.294
I did. He's hot, come on.

26:38.296 --> 26:41.497
You're always trying
to make light of things.

26:41.499 --> 26:43.833
Why don't you tell me
how you really feel?

26:43.835 --> 26:45.735
I am tell--
What, you don't think

26:45.737 --> 26:47.269
I'm telling you how
I really feel?

26:47.271 --> 26:49.739
No, I don't.

26:49.741 --> 26:53.976
You use irony and humor
as a defensive shield.

26:53.978 --> 26:55.111
You know, I--

26:55.113 --> 26:57.913
Doesn't that just
become exhausting?

26:57.915 --> 27:00.282
Yeah.

27:00.284 --> 27:04.553
But my wit
has become my blankie.

27:04.555 --> 27:06.789
Come on.

27:06.791 --> 27:08.224
All right, I did--

27:08.226 --> 27:10.493
I enjoyed seeing him
read his own poem.

27:10.495 --> 27:11.727
"Seeking a cause."

27:11.729 --> 27:14.864
Yes, that last line really
got me, what was it, um--

27:14.866 --> 27:17.833
"He died
never finding the cause

27:17.835 --> 27:20.836
because he never knew
he was the cause?"

27:21.873 --> 27:22.905
That was powerful.

27:22.907 --> 27:24.373
It was.

27:24.375 --> 27:25.508
I thought that was powerful.

27:25.510 --> 27:30.246
I feel like Mary Jane
knows her cause, you know?

27:30.248 --> 27:33.015
<i>You</i> know your cause.

27:33.017 --> 27:38.821
John has my kids and I don't
know what my cause is.

27:38.823 --> 27:44.427
I don't know
what my reason for being is.

27:44.429 --> 27:47.196
All I do is work.

27:47.198 --> 27:49.265
I'm like a robot,
I go to work.

27:49.267 --> 27:51.267
And after what happened today,

27:51.269 --> 27:54.437
I've just been like
questioning everything.

27:54.439 --> 27:55.439
I feel...

27:56.773 --> 27:58.474
It's--

27:58.476 --> 28:00.976
I think maybe I just need
to find my cause, right?

28:00.978 --> 28:03.412
I think that's what it's about.

28:03.414 --> 28:07.550
Maybe you're your own cause.

28:09.219 --> 28:10.419
Maybe.

28:10.421 --> 28:15.257
You'll find out why you feel
you're so unlovable.

28:16.526 --> 28:18.294
Get out of my head.

28:18.296 --> 28:19.795
Maybe--

28:22.632 --> 28:24.033
I'm your cause.

28:24.035 --> 28:28.471
You are a hot mess cause.

28:33.243 --> 28:36.579
There are things
that never change

28:36.581 --> 28:41.150
and we are not one of them,
I fear.

28:41.152 --> 28:45.955
The trouble with
our love is here.

28:45.957 --> 28:48.591
The trouble with
our love is round

28:48.593 --> 28:52.261
when you cannot look me
in the eye and lie.

28:52.263 --> 28:55.164
When you run
so far away you forget

28:55.166 --> 28:57.266
where to get back to.

29:00.604 --> 29:05.441
Now... you are

29:05.443 --> 29:07.776
what you never wanted to be.

29:11.882 --> 29:14.917
Go ahead.

29:14.919 --> 29:16.352
Bite me.

29:59.429 --> 30:01.363
<i>Hello?</i> Hey, Mark.

30:01.365 --> 30:03.165
I can't be here by myself.

30:03.167 --> 30:04.867
You wanna come to
this party with me?

30:04.869 --> 30:08.070
Hell, yeah, you know what?

30:08.072 --> 30:10.606
I do not wanna be here
alone tonight, either?

30:10.608 --> 30:13.976
Let's go get stupid ass...

30:13.978 --> 30:15.878
<i>...drunk.</i>

30:15.880 --> 30:17.046
All right, I'll call you
when I'm ready.

30:17.048 --> 30:19.048
Okay. <i> Bye.</i>

30:30.327 --> 30:31.527
Yeah.

30:31.529 --> 30:34.430
This is how you throw
a dinner party, okay?

30:34.432 --> 30:35.464
I need a raise.

30:35.466 --> 30:38.634
We live in Section 8 housing,
Mary Jane?

30:38.636 --> 30:40.135
I like how
you keep surprising me.

30:40.137 --> 30:42.004
Oh, what woman
could deny you, Sheldon?

30:42.006 --> 30:43.105
This is--

30:43.107 --> 30:45.374
Mark Bradley,
pleasure to meet you.

30:45.376 --> 30:46.742
Same, I heard
a lot about you.

30:46.744 --> 30:48.077
Really? Yes.

30:48.079 --> 30:52.615
Come, I want you to meet
some amazing friends of mine.

31:29.252 --> 31:31.220
Hey, guys.

31:31.222 --> 31:33.856
Ladies, gather 'round.

31:33.858 --> 31:36.725
I just wanna thank you all
for coming.

31:36.727 --> 31:39.395
Most of you know who I am,
the lucky ones don't.

31:40.798 --> 31:42.998
Uh, I don't even know
how I got into this.

31:43.000 --> 31:44.133
The last thing I remember,

31:44.135 --> 31:45.734
I was asking Chuck
what he and Shelly

31:45.736 --> 31:49.538
were going to do for their
anniversary of 25 years!

31:52.792 --> 31:54.626
And he said Shelly
just wants to go out to dinner.

31:54.628 --> 31:57.496
I said, "No! You gotta
celebrate, come on."

31:57.498 --> 32:00.566
And the next thing I know,
I'm staring at you people.

32:00.568 --> 32:03.202
Chuck, Shelly, never known
two greater friends,

32:03.204 --> 32:04.570
I love you.

32:04.572 --> 32:05.671
Chuck, you owe me for life

32:05.673 --> 32:06.672
because I told you
she was the one.

32:06.674 --> 32:08.707
To Chuck and Shelly.

32:08.709 --> 32:10.459
Chuck and Shelly!

32:16.249 --> 32:19.618
Oh, look at that, whoa.

32:21.188 --> 32:22.588
It looks great.

32:25.325 --> 32:26.825
Daddy, is this legal?

32:26.827 --> 32:27.860
Legal?

32:27.862 --> 32:29.328
What do you mean, legal?

32:29.330 --> 32:30.596
It's not my birthday.

32:30.598 --> 32:31.897
So what.

32:31.899 --> 32:34.133
The day of your birth was
the best day of my life.

32:34.135 --> 32:36.468
We can celebrate it
any day we want.

32:36.470 --> 32:38.537
Even on your birthday?

32:38.539 --> 32:40.305
Even on my birthday.

32:40.307 --> 32:42.808
Happy birthday, Daddy.

32:42.810 --> 32:45.110
Mmm, happy birthday, baby.

32:56.523 --> 32:57.689
Was that Mommy?

32:57.691 --> 32:59.491
No.

32:59.493 --> 33:04.263
But we're gonna have some fun
together until she comes home.

33:04.265 --> 33:06.331
And when is she coming home?

33:06.333 --> 33:09.835
I don't know.

33:09.837 --> 33:11.070
But I'm gonna
be there for you

33:11.072 --> 33:12.838
and with you every day,
all right?

33:12.840 --> 33:13.972
All right.
You'll never be alone again,

33:13.974 --> 33:15.707
I promise.

33:15.709 --> 33:17.843
Give me some sugar.
I love you, Daddy.

33:17.845 --> 33:19.078
Mmm, I love you too, baby.

33:19.080 --> 33:20.746
Oh, you got me.

33:21.782 --> 33:23.449
Hey, no.

33:23.451 --> 33:25.017
Want some cake?

33:25.019 --> 33:27.052
Yeah. All right.

33:27.054 --> 33:28.687
Thank you.

33:30.557 --> 33:31.924
Oh, well,

33:31.926 --> 33:35.127
here's to being abandoned
at someone else's party.

33:35.129 --> 33:36.195
When you're in town,

33:36.197 --> 33:37.696
you should ride
the Ferris wheel.

33:37.698 --> 33:39.531
Great city views.

33:39.533 --> 33:41.633
I'll leave the tourist stuff
to the tourists.

33:41.635 --> 33:43.469
I'm only in town
for two more days.

33:43.471 --> 33:44.970
Where's a decent bar?

33:44.972 --> 33:47.372
Where do you go in Seattle?

33:47.374 --> 33:49.608
Uh, Eagle.

33:49.610 --> 33:50.610
Have you heard of it?

33:52.145 --> 33:54.604
We have an Eagle here
in Atlanta, you should go.

33:56.416 --> 33:57.583
I will.

34:06.493 --> 34:08.427
This is exactly what I needed.

34:08.429 --> 34:10.329
Thank you for getting me
out of the house.

34:10.331 --> 34:13.599
Oh, thank you for elevating
the cool factor of the party.

34:15.534 --> 34:16.969
Would you please wear
that dress again.

34:16.971 --> 34:19.004
You're giving me stirrings?

34:19.005 --> 34:20.304
Stirrings?

34:20.306 --> 34:23.108
Wow, you really like
to use your vocabulary words.

34:23.110 --> 34:24.342
There's a few words
I can come up with

34:24.344 --> 34:26.411
to describe what I'd like
to do with you in that dress

34:26.413 --> 34:28.045
right here in front
of everybody.

34:28.047 --> 34:29.281
Uh, you know,

34:29.283 --> 34:32.351
I think I feel safer
around you over the phone.

34:32.353 --> 34:35.353
Oxymoron, I heard it,
I know, thank you.

34:35.356 --> 34:36.822
I haven't been
drinking, have I?

34:36.824 --> 34:38.257
Oh, just a touch.

34:40.293 --> 34:41.460
What I mean to say is

34:41.462 --> 34:43.996
I'm relationship whipped.

34:43.998 --> 34:46.264
I don't wanna rush
into anything.

34:46.266 --> 34:49.368
You're in luck,
I'm a patient man.

34:49.370 --> 34:51.335
And you're well worth the wait.

34:52.871 --> 34:54.206
Drink up, have fun.

34:54.208 --> 34:57.776
If you have too much,
I'll call you a car.

34:57.778 --> 35:01.380
Well, then, please have
your server pour me another.

35:01.382 --> 35:02.614
Sure.

35:13.177 --> 35:16.478
♪ Guess it's true I'm not good
at a one-night stand ♪

35:16.480 --> 35:17.513
What are you doing?

35:18.883 --> 35:23.986
♪ But I still need love
'cause I'm just a man ♪

35:23.988 --> 35:29.458
♪ These nights never
seem to go to plan ♪

35:29.460 --> 35:33.695
♪ I don't want you to leave
will you hold my hand ♪

35:33.697 --> 35:39.001
♪ Oh won't you stay with me? ♪

35:39.003 --> 35:44.606
♪ 'Cause you're all I need ♪

35:44.608 --> 35:49.611
♪ This ain't love
it's clear to see ♪

35:49.613 --> 35:53.849
♪ But darling stay with me ♪

35:57.086 --> 36:00.322
♪ Why am I so emotional? ♪

36:02.125 --> 36:06.995
♪ This is not a good look
gain some self-control ♪

36:06.997 --> 36:12.301
♪ And deep down
I know this never works ♪

36:12.303 --> 36:16.505
♪ But you can lay with me
so it doesn't hurt ♪

36:16.507 --> 36:22.444
♪ Oh won't you stay with me? ♪

36:22.446 --> 36:27.849
♪ 'Cause you're all I need ♪

36:27.851 --> 36:32.287
♪ This ain't love
it's clear to see ♪

36:32.289 --> 36:33.822
♪ But darling ♪

36:33.824 --> 36:35.591
Hi, I'm home, I'm sorry.

36:35.593 --> 36:37.292
I assume you were kidnapped.

36:37.294 --> 36:39.428
Yeah, I know,
I was supposed to call you

36:39.430 --> 36:41.330
<i>when I got home,</i>
<i>and I got tired.</i>

36:41.332 --> 36:42.331
And it sort of
slipped my mind.

36:42.333 --> 36:43.532
<i>No worries.</i>

36:43.534 --> 36:46.368
I'm often accused
of having the same problem.

36:48.204 --> 36:51.106
I had a really great time
tonight, thank you.

36:51.108 --> 36:52.240
Your friends are amazing.

36:52.242 --> 36:54.977
They feel
the same about you.

36:54.979 --> 36:57.012
You really shine around people,
you know that?

36:57.014 --> 36:59.414
Well, I'm looking forward
to the next time.

36:59.416 --> 37:01.216
Oh, I get a next time.

37:01.218 --> 37:02.584
Yeah, I owe you.

37:04.220 --> 37:06.221
Well, then I'll try
to step it up for next time.

37:07.657 --> 37:08.690
Listen, I know it's getting late

37:08.692 --> 37:10.559
and you have
to work tomorrow, so...

37:12.328 --> 37:15.797
Okay. Um, bye.

37:15.799 --> 37:18.066
Good night.

37:18.068 --> 37:21.003
♪ Stay with me ♪

37:21.005 --> 37:24.139
♪ Ohh ♪

37:24.141 --> 37:25.407
Are you still there?

37:25.409 --> 37:28.043
Yes.

37:28.045 --> 37:30.312
One last question.

37:32.548 --> 37:34.116
"Godfather" one or two?

37:36.285 --> 37:37.919
Uh, um... wow.

37:37.921 --> 37:39.905
"Godfather" one was a classic.

37:39.907 --> 37:43.158
But Coppola really got
the recipe right with two.

37:43.160 --> 37:44.359
Choose.

37:44.361 --> 37:46.528
Oh, you have me though,
one under protest.

37:46.530 --> 37:49.498
Uh, beach or mountains?

37:49.500 --> 37:51.166
Beach.

37:51.168 --> 37:53.135
I look amazing in a bikini.

37:53.137 --> 37:55.303
Ooh, I can only imagine.

37:55.305 --> 37:57.606
Maybe you won't
have to imagine.

37:57.608 --> 38:00.142
Well, sookie sookie now.
Oh, please don't do that.

38:00.144 --> 38:02.244
'80s or '90s?

38:04.347 --> 38:05.747
♪ Oh won't you ♪

38:05.749 --> 38:06.782
'90s.

38:06.784 --> 38:08.116
♪ Stay with me ♪

38:08.118 --> 38:10.118
♪ Won't you stay,
won't you stay ♪
